entry.title: Ignore OCR results if PDF Accessibility Tree gets updated during OCR.
entry.content:
If PdfAccessibilityTree finds images without alternative text, it sends

them to OCR service to be converted to text. But while OCR is running,

the tree may get updated for various reasons including changes in a11y

settings. If this happens, the id of the image node and its parent will

change and once OCR results are ready, they cannot be inserted into the

updated tree.

If this scenario happens, OCR results are just ignored.

entry.title: Cleanup GetTransform methods in OpenXrController
entry.content:
Based upon its (correct) assignment to XrInputSourceDescription's

input_from_pointer member, the `GetPointerFromGripTransform` method is

inaccurately named, since the current name implies that it returns

`pointer_from_grip` while actually it returns `grip_from_pointer`

(`input_from_pointer` is perhaps a bit unfortunately named, and `grip`

can be used interchangeably with how it uses `input`). This change

thus renames the method to `GetGripFromPointerTransform`, which is more

accurate.



Some of this confusion likely came from the ambiguously named

`GetTransformFromSpaces` method, which *does* indeed return the

`origin_from_target` transform. This method was *also* renamed to be

more clear, to `GetOriginFromTarget`. In doing so, the order of the

spaces passed in was also swapped so that the order matched the new

method name. This was only called by two methods locally, and verified

via WMR that they were both flipped appropriately. This method also

did not access any local state and was abstracte to an anonymous

namespace function, which would better facilitate moving it out of this

class if that becomes necessary in the future.

entry.title: StatusAreaTester: Constructs fake model in the handler
entry.content:
Create a fake model in StatusAreaInternalsHandler that is used when the

tester is in used. When the tester is closed, we will switch back to use

the real model created by Shell. With this way, we can configure the

information displayed in the Quick Settings. In this CL we add a way to

entry.title: [Responsive Toolbar] Fix animating layout bug.
entry.content:
Animating layout could get stuck in a state where its current layout

size was zero, which meant it was never rendered, which meant it never

had a chance to invalidate and recalculate its preferred size.



This resulted in a fully-collapsed animating layout embedded in a flex

layout when it was first rendered (e.g. a ToolbarIconContainer in a

narrow browser window) never being able to un-collapse and show its

contents, even if the browser window was made larger.



This CL bypasses the "does the current layout fit in the available

space?" check if the current layout is empty in the default

AnimatingLayoutManager flex rule.



This means if the current layout is empty, the flex rule returns the

correct size for e.g. _x_ and _x0 queries, which are important in the

initial FlexLayout setup.



Bug: 1506607

entry.title: [mullet m2] Maximum popup width is respected.
entry.content:
problem: When adding labels to the popup, we make it so that

each individual label has the max width equals to the popup max width.

Since there can be more than one label per row, this leads to a popup

whose width is larger than its expected max value.



solution:



1. Make `FormatLabel` receive the width as param.

2. In the label case, divide the width by the number of labels in

the row.



notes:



1. Granular filling feature introduces a new max width to the label.

2. This change is no-op to the current behaviour.

entry.title: [css-variables] Count ‚Äú--foo: initial‚Äù as a style declaration.
entry.content:
When the current system of independent inheritance-like behavior

for custom properties was written, the ComputedStyle was marked as

having a variable declaration from fairly deep down in Resolve().

However, if using ‚Äúinitial‚Äù (or ‚Äúinherit‚Äù, but that should be

irrelevant for this discussion), Resolve() would never be called,

and the ComputedStyle would erroneously be counted as not having

a variable declaration. Thus, independent inheritance would not

be properly stopped for such elements, leading to wrong results

in some recalcs.



Fix by setting the property in CustomProperty::Apply* instead,

which seems like a more logical place to begin with. (We could

also apply it in StyleBuilder::ApplyPhysicalProperty() if we

wish to have it only one place, but it would require an extra

test there that would be irrelevant for most properties.)

entry.title: Missing ::first-letter style update for size queries
entry.content:
Style for ::first-letter pseudo elements are updated as late as possible

to allow nodes to re-attach to make sure any first-letter text node

changes are included when computing style for the first rendered letter.



When the StyleRecalcChange were already marked for ReattachLayoutTree()

when reaching the ::first-letter update, we assumed some ancestor of the

::first-letter element would be re-attached, and the ::first-letter

style being updated in Element::AttachLayoutTree() for the originating

element. But, if the originating element was a size container, and we

skipped style recalc for its descendants, we would mark the stored

StyleRecalcChange for re-attachment of the children when resuming, even

if the originating element itself would be re-attached.



Instead, check that we also did not suppress style recalc for the

originating element for the ::first-letter before skipping its style

update during style recalc.



Bug: 1505250

entry.title: [mullet m3] Add PopupType::kAutocomplete for popup showing autocomplete.
entry.content:
PopupType is computed based on the passed form, field and triggering

source. Autocomplete suggestions are shown when we can't generate other

suggestion types. The PopupType is not updated in AED in this case.

This means that AED::GetPopupType() can return arbitrary value when

autocomplete suggestions are shown.



This CL adds a dedicated PopupType::kAutocomplete to be used when

autocomplete suggestions are shown. This requires updating all places

where PopupType is used:



* ChromeAutofillClient::ShowAutofillSettings - can't be called when AC

suggestions are shown -> no changes required.

* suggestions_list_metrics::LogAutofillSelectedManageEntry - can't be

logged when AC suggestions are shown -> no changes required.

* popup_cell_utils::FormatLabel - can be called when AC suggestions

are shown -> add formatting for autocomplete suggestion labels.

* FormInputAccessoryViewController::announceVoiceOverMessageIfNeeded -

uses different AX labels - add new autocomplete AX label.

* CreditCardAutofillTouchBarController::initWithController - has special

logic for credit card popup type - no changes required for autocomplete.



Next steps: override PopupType in AED when autocomplete suggestions are

shown.
